# Hypixel SkyBlock Bazaar: `sell_summary` vs `buy_summary`

Source: `https://api.hypixel.net/v2/skyblock/bazaar` → `products[product_id]`.

**Wither Shield scroll** product id: `WITHER_SHIELD_SCROLL` (Shadow Warp / Implosion: `SHADOW_WARP_SCROLL`, `IMPLOSION_SCROLL`).

**Rule:** For the same item at the same time, **instant buy price is always higher than instant sell price** (you pay more to buy now than you receive to sell now).

| API field | Per-unit meaning | Player term |
|-----------|------------------|-------------|
| `buy_summary[0].pricePerUnit` | Price to **buy** from the bazaar **now** | **Instant buy** (higher) |
| `sell_summary[0].pricePerUnit` | Price you get **selling** to the bazaar **now** | **Instant sell** (lower) |

In this repo (legacy names — read the JSDoc in `src/lib/bazaar.ts`):

- `bazaarInstantSell()` reads **`buy_summary[0]`** → **instant buy** (higher). Name is misleading.
- `bazaarSellSummaryFirst()` reads **`sell_summary[0]`** → **instant sell** (lower).

Hyperion **calculator** WIMP: `scrollsInstantBuy === true` uses `bazaarInstantSell` → **instant buy** (higher). `false` uses `bazaarSellSummaryFirst` → **instant sell** (lower).
